text: I had pork chop for take away at $8.20. The taste and portion was good. Order was easy and service was fast. Enjoyed the meal.

Food was a good portion for $7 (fish and chips) and $7 (chicken chop). Fish was thick and juicy, fries were a tad too salty but overall a good experience. Bonus: the teh c Peng siu dai at the drinks stall is good!
Come here if you are looking for old school western food that tastes good! Full of flavour and at an affordable range. I had the Chicken Chop set for SGD7 and the portion was huge!
If you're looking for old school Singaporean-style western food for some nostalgia, you will not be disappointed!
$7 for portion shown here. Not bad nothing to complain about. Chicken Chop set.
